<i>at the time Sue was discovered.</i>

706
00:36:17,907 --> 00:36:20,910
In 1992, I was working
at "Unsolved Mysteries,"

707
00:36:20,911 --> 00:36:22,511
a TV show on NBC,

708
00:36:22,512 --> 00:36:24,613
researching cases where people

709
00:36:24,614 --> 00:36:26,915
convicted of crimes
insist they were innocent.

710
00:36:26,916 --> 00:36:29,618
And that first day
the dinosaur was seized,

711
00:36:29,619 --> 00:36:31,821
Pete called me on the phone
in the middle of it all.

712
00:36:32,021 --> 00:36:34,689
He said the FBI was here,

713
00:36:34,690 --> 00:36:38,560
and it was dramatic and scary,

714
00:36:38,561 --> 00:36:41,964
and he needed coverage.
He needed support.

715
00:36:41,965 --> 00:36:44,734
So I thought, well,
I'll go cover the story

716
00:36:44,735 --> 00:36:46,768
and take a hiatus

717
00:36:46,769 --> 00:36:49,504
and maybe move away
from L.A. forever.

718
00:36:49,505 --> 00:36:51,473
I didn't know,
but I just packed up

719
00:36:51,474 --> 00:36:52,808
and bailed back to South Dakota

720
00:36:52,809 --> 00:36:55,343
by the end of the year
to cover the story and see

721
00:36:55,344 --> 00:36:56,818
what was gonna happen to it.

722
00:36:59,290 --> 00:37:01,817
America's Indian tribes
have fought the white man

723
00:37:01,818 --> 00:37:03,821
over many different
issues through the years,

724
00:37:04,021 --> 00:37:06,429
but the newest fight
is over a dinosaur.

725
00:37:12,429 --> 00:37:13,529
<i>It was a big story</i>

726
00:37:13,530 --> 00:37:14,696
<i>and a very unusual story.</i>

727
00:37:14,697 --> 00:37:17,066
To have the federal
government come in

728
00:37:17,067 --> 00:37:18,701
and seize Sue,

729
00:37:18,702 --> 00:37:20,803
- everything exploded.
- Controversy tonight.

730
00:37:20,804 --> 00:37:22,437
Controversy surrounding
the Institute

731
00:37:22,438 --> 00:37:23,839
and their most famous discovery.

732
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:26,308
It may be the custody
battle of the century...

733
00:37:26,309 --> 00:37:27,977
scientists, Indians,
the U.S. government.

734
00:37:27,978 --> 00:37:29,611
You find any fossils,

735
00:37:29,612 --> 00:37:31,413
the government
may take them away.

736
00:37:31,414 --> 00:37:33,316
Not only has he taken
this dinosaur away,

737
00:37:33,317 --> 00:37:34,984
but he's taken our
research away too,

738
00:37:34,985 --> 00:37:37,852
every photograph, every record
we had about this dinosaur

739
00:37:37,853 --> 00:37:39,421
and the locality
where she was found.

740
00:37:39,422 --> 00:37:41,624
Sue was seized pursuant
to a search warrant,

741
00:37:41,625 --> 00:37:43,859
but there was never
a crime charged.

742
00:37:43,860 --> 00:37:46,995
Pat and I talked
about filing suit.

743
00:37:46,996 --> 00:37:48,730
You know, we sued the
federal government

744
00:37:48,731 --> 00:37:50,153
for return of our property.

745
00:37:52,101 --> 00:37:53,768
<i>The Black Hills Institute</i>

746
00:37:53,769 --> 00:37:56,738
said it purchased the fossil
from Maurice Williams.

747
00:37:56,739 --> 00:37:59,607
Originally Maurice
Williams said that too,

748
00:37:59,608 --> 00:38:01,776
but then he changed his claim,

749
00:38:01,777 --> 00:38:03,946
and he said he had
not sold the fossil

750
00:38:03,947 --> 00:38:05,915
and that he owned it.

751
00:38:05,916 --> 00:38:07,018
Mr. Williams...

752
00:38:08,018 --> 00:38:09,752
<i>Pete and Neal had</i>

753
00:38:09,753 --> 00:38:12,620
<i>made a deal with Maurice
Williams for $5,000.</i>

754
00:38:12,621 --> 00:38:14,556
<i>On that Saturday,</i>

755
00:38:14,557 --> 00:38:16,877
<i>the day before we finished
getting Sue out of the ground,</i>

756
00:38:16,878 --> 00:38:19,761
<i>that we gave Maurice
Williams a check for $5,000,</i>

757
00:38:19,762 --> 00:38:21,596
<i>that said for "Theropod Sue"</i>

758
00:38:21,597 --> 00:38:22,997
<i>on the bottom of the check.</i>

759
00:38:22,998 --> 00:38:24,866
<i>Even though $5,000 may
not seem like a lot,</i>

760
00:38:24,867 --> 00:38:27,535
it was a lot of money for
our company to spend,

761
00:38:27,536 --> 00:38:30,071
<i>and no one had ever
paid that much</i>

762
00:38:30,072 --> 00:38:32,640
<i>for an undiscovered
fossil before.</i>

763
00:38:32,641 --> 00:38:35,044
<i>We had lots of conversations
with Maurice Williams</i>

764
00:38:35,045 --> 00:38:37,379
<i>about what was happening
to the dinosaur.</i>

765
00:38:37,380 --> 00:38:39,620
<i>He knew that we were going to
bring it back to Hill City.</i>

766
00:38:39,621 --> 00:38:41,082
<i>He was completely
in favor of that.</i>

767
00:38:41,083 --> 00:38:42,917
<i>He knew about the museum
we were building.</i>

768
00:38:42,918 --> 00:38:44,986
<i>He knew we were going to
be preparing the fossil.</i>

769
00:38:44,987 --> 00:38:47,040
<i>That's about the only
ones that we have.</i>

770
00:38:53,356 --> 00:38:54,830
<i>Well, it's not the only one.</i>

771
00:38:54,831 --> 00:38:56,131
<i>- Almost.
- Almost.</i>

772
00:38:56,132 --> 00:38:57,972
<i>And it's not...
not completely...</i>

773
00:39:11,648 --> 00:39:13,948
<i>Maurice Williams never intended</i>

774
00:39:13,949 --> 00:39:16,951
<i>to sell that fossil.</i>

775
00:39:16,952 --> 00:39:19,955
Maurice Williams knew
exactly what he was doing.

776
00:39:19,956 --> 00:39:21,924
Numerous people
said, "Had we known

777
00:39:21,925 --> 00:39:23,959
you were on his ranch, we
would have warned you."

778
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:25,560
<i>I had known people</i>

779
00:39:25,561 --> 00:39:26,962
<i>who knew Maurice and Sharky,</i>

780
00:39:26,963 --> 00:39:28,564
<i>and they were colorful</i>

781
00:39:28,565 --> 00:39:29,631
<i>and controversial figures</i>

782
00:39:29,632 --> 00:39:30,732
<i>in their own right</i>

783
00:39:30,733 --> 00:39:32,577
on the Cheyenne River
Reservation.

784
00:39:41,577 --> 00:39:44,046
There began to emerge
some controversy

785
00:39:44,047 --> 00:39:47,683
about Sue being
collected from Indian land

786
00:39:47,684 --> 00:39:48,948
and the ownership issue.

787
00:40:09,572 --> 00:40:12,241
<i>You could not have
discovered this rex</i>

788
00:40:12,242 --> 00:40:16,611
in a worse and potentially

789
00:40:16,612 --> 00:40:18,186
legally complicated place.

790
00:40:23,186 --> 00:40:24,787
<i>It was discovered</i>

791
00:40:24,788 --> 00:40:26,187
<i>within the exterior boundaries</i>

792
00:40:26,188 --> 00:40:28,089
<i>of the Cheyenne River
Sioux tribe</i>

793
00:40:28,090 --> 00:40:32,627
<i>on land which was held in trust</i>

794
00:40:32,628 --> 00:40:35,196
<i>for the benefit of Maurice
Williams, the landowner.</i>

795
00:40:35,197 --> 00:40:36,799
<i>Wasn't tribal land.</i>

796
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:39,134
It wasn't federal land.

797
00:40:39,135 --> 00:40:41,504
It was a really...

798
00:40:41,505 --> 00:40:42,904
Sue came out

799
00:40:42,905 --> 00:40:46,614
from an absolute
legal netherworld.

800
00:40:50,392 --> 00:40:51,814
<i>Indian people were given...</i>

801
00:40:52,014 --> 00:40:54,950
<i>heads of household
were given 160 acres</i>

802
00:40:54,951 --> 00:40:58,821
<i>in what we call
the Allotment Acts.</i>

803
00:40:58,822 --> 00:41:00,288
And that was to try

804
00:41:00,289 --> 00:41:02,524
and make people
who didn't understand

805
00:41:02,525 --> 00:41:04,627
land ownership
be owners of land,

806
00:41:04,628 --> 00:41:06,028
but they really
didn't own the land.

807
00:41:06,029 --> 00:41:08,230
So there became this concept

808
00:41:08,231 --> 00:41:10,098
of trust responsibility,

809
00:41:10,099 --> 00:41:13,935
and nothing ostensibly is
supposed to happen to that land

810
00:41:13,936 --> 00:41:15,770
without the approval
of the federal government

811
00:41:15,771 --> 00:41:17,876
through the Bureau
of Indian Affairs.

812
00:41:20,876 --> 00:41:22,578
<i>On the reservations,</i>

813
00:41:22,579 --> 00:41:24,299
<i>the United States holds
that land in trust</i>

814
00:41:24,300 --> 00:41:27,249
<i>for the individual Indian
as the beneficiary.</i>

815
00:41:27,250 --> 00:41:30,252
And the United States

816
00:41:30,253 --> 00:41:32,687
has a fiduciary responsibility

817
00:41:32,688 --> 00:41:35,790
to individual Indians
and/or their families.

818
00:41:35,791 --> 00:41:38,318
that they get the highest
and best use out of it.

819
00:41:41,597 --> 00:41:43,064
<i>All across the West,</i>

820
00:41:43,065 --> 00:41:46,968
<i>it is a patchwork quilt
of laws and regulations</i>

821
00:41:46,969 --> 00:41:49,971
<i>concerning what can
and can't be harvested</i>

822
00:41:49,972 --> 00:41:51,277
<i>that's paleontological.</i>

823
00:41:54,277 --> 00:41:57,245
<i>You can be all right in
this quarter section,</i>

824
00:41:57,246 --> 00:41:58,980
but if you get off
a little bit...

825
00:41:58,981 --> 00:42:00,982
remember this is before GPS.

826
00:42:00,983 --> 00:42:03,151
If you get off a little
bit to the wrong place,

827
00:42:03,152 --> 00:42:05,754
you might be dealing with a whole
'nother set of regulations.

828
00:42:05,755 --> 00:42:08,756
The tribe claimed that
because Maurice Williams,

829
00:42:08,757 --> 00:42:11,225
being a member of the tribe,

830
00:42:11,226 --> 00:42:13,127
had not purchased

831
00:42:13,128 --> 00:42:16,098
a $100 permit to sell something,

832
00:42:16,099 --> 00:42:17,966
the fossil should be forfeited

833
00:42:17,967 --> 00:42:20,069
and therefore
they owned the fossil.

834
00:42:20,070 --> 00:42:21,669
And of course
the government said

835
00:42:21,670 --> 00:42:23,071
that it was government property

836
00:42:23,072 --> 00:42:26,150
and that that was because
of the trust land issue.

837
00:42:34,150 --> 00:42:36,352
The seizure and the subpoena

838
00:42:36,353 --> 00:42:38,386
were the brainchild

839
00:42:38,387 --> 00:42:40,888
of Acting U.S. Attorney
Kevin Schieffer.

840
00:42:40,889 --> 00:42:42,290
<i>He was a controversial</i>

841
00:42:42,291 --> 00:42:44,292
<i>figure as
a U.S. Attorney,</i>

842
00:42:44,293 --> 00:42:48,296
<i>because he hadn't had lot of
experience practicing law.</i>

843
00:42:48,297 --> 00:42:50,666
He had the ability to
drive some people crazy.

844
00:42:50,866 --> 00:42:53,134
I do have a fair amount
of litigation experience.

845
00:42:53,135 --> 00:42:56,138
I have not had
courtroom experience.

846
00:42:56,139 --> 00:42:57,245
<i>It's a little unclear</i>

847
00:42:58,007 --> 00:43:02,410
as to why Schieffer
decided to seize Sue

848
00:43:02,411 --> 00:43:04,346
or decided to become
interested in this at all,

849
00:43:04,347 --> 00:43:06,214
<i>whether it began
with Maurice Williams</i>

850
00:43:06,215 --> 00:43:08,183
<i>or a complaint from the tribe.</i>

851
00:43:08,184 --> 00:43:11,654
<i>Ultimately the decision was
Kevin Schieffer's, though,</i>

852
00:43:11,655 --> 00:43:15,996
<i>to decide that this was something
that they wanted to do.</i>

853
00:43:20,596 --> 00:43:22,916
<i>Also was shocking from a
scientific standpoint,</i>

854
00:43:22,917 --> 00:43:24,785
<i>that anybody would
behave so recklessly</i>

855
00:43:24,786 --> 00:43:27,435
with the greatest paleontological
find of all time.

856
00:43:27,436 --> 00:43:29,203
If that dinosaur seizure

857
00:43:29,204 --> 00:43:30,805
wasn't a publicity stunt,

858
00:43:30,806 --> 00:43:32,306
then I don't know what is.

859
00:43:32,307 --> 00:43:34,676
There could have been
a gang in this town

860
00:43:34,677 --> 00:43:36,678
with a warehouse
holding a ton of cocaine

861
00:43:36,679 --> 00:43:38,747
and human bodies
hanging from the rafters,

862
00:43:38,748 --> 00:43:40,548
and the federal government
would not have sent

863
00:43:40,549 --> 00:43:43,251
35 agents
and the National Guard.

864
00:43:51,827 --> 00:43:54,163
<i>Just a few of 'em.
Bumper stickers?</i>

865
00:43:54,164 --> 00:43:55,863
<i>There's some in every vehicle.</i>

866
00:43:55,864 --> 00:43:58,767
We would just like to gain
public support for our cause

867
00:43:58,768 --> 00:44:00,736
of getting Sue
back to Hill City.

868
00:44:00,737 --> 00:44:03,337
<i>When you get the big foot
of the government come in</i>

869
00:44:03,338 --> 00:44:05,941
<i>and do something like that,
you better answer</i>

870
00:44:05,942 --> 00:44:07,382
<i>in a way that people
can understand</i>

871
00:44:07,383 --> 00:44:08,944
<i>that this is wrong.</i>

872
00:44:08,945 --> 00:44:11,379
You know, they just protested
for three straight days

873
00:44:11,380 --> 00:44:14,116
in front of the Institute
during the raid.

874
00:44:14,117 --> 00:44:15,718
They weren't done.

875
00:44:15,719 --> 00:44:17,252
"We want to protest."

876
00:44:17,253 --> 00:44:19,822
Okay. Let's go protest.

877
00:44:31,768 --> 00:44:33,938
Stay back.

878
00:44:34,938 --> 00:44:36,337
Everyone stay back.

879
00:44:36,338 --> 00:44:38,406
You'll be thrown to the
ground and arrested.

880
00:44:38,407 --> 00:44:40,241
We got everything
under control here.

881
00:44:40,242 --> 00:44:41,843
We don't want any trouble.

882
00:44:41,844 --> 00:44:43,745
<i>We had people from
all over the community,</i>

883
00:44:43,746 --> 00:44:45,413
all over the Black Hills
trying to help,

884
00:44:45,414 --> 00:44:47,750
<i>and it was amazing,
the support that we had.</i>

885
00:44:47,751 --> 00:44:50,151
We were fighting on every
front we could think of,

886
00:44:50,152 --> 00:44:51,787
everything that you
could think of,

887
00:44:51,788 --> 00:44:53,455
<i>everything from
the Sue Freedom Run</i>

888
00:44:53,456 --> 00:44:55,790
<i>to petitions we took
to the state capitol.</i>

889
00:44:55,791 --> 00:44:58,459
<i>I would talk in front
of groups anywhere.</i>

890
00:44:58,460 --> 00:45:00,796
<i>Terry was so involved</i>

891
00:45:00,797 --> 00:45:02,833
<i>in this case.
I mean, he lived it.</i>

892
00:45:04,827 --> 00:45:07,301
<i>One of the most moving
things in my life to see,</i>

893
00:45:07,302 --> 00:45:09,171
<i>this wonderful group
of people here</i>

894
00:45:09,172 --> 00:45:10,782
supported us getting Sue back.

895
00:45:19,782 --> 00:45:22,317
The U.S. Attorney,
Mr. Kevin Schieffer,

896
00:45:22,318 --> 00:45:24,453
made a terrible error

897
00:45:24,454 --> 00:45:27,455
in coming that tragic day
on May 14th to Hill City.

898
00:45:27,456 --> 00:45:29,258
The right thing to do
in this case

899
00:45:29,259 --> 00:45:31,575
would be to return the
dinosaur to Hill City.

900
00:45:33,396 --> 00:45:35,129
<i>Whoa! Yes, yes!</i>

901
00:45:35,130 --> 00:45:36,330
<i>Whoo!</i>

902
00:45:36,331 --> 00:45:38,366
<i>We got now
over 20,000 signatures</i>

903
00:45:38,367 --> 00:45:39,968
<i>on the one petition,</i>

904
00:45:39,969 --> 00:45:42,037
the first petition
to bring Sue back,

905
00:45:42,038 --> 00:45:43,471
and they're from all 50 states

906
00:45:43,472 --> 00:45:45,339
and from 14 other countries.

907
00:45:45,340 --> 00:45:47,475
<i>Lot of people didn't have
a lot of money here,</i>

908
00:45:47,476 --> 00:45:49,757
<i>so they wanted to contribute
any way they could do that,</i>

909
00:45:49,758 --> 00:45:51,078
<i>and so there were a lot</i>

910
00:45:51,079 --> 00:45:52,948
<i>of fund-raisers, parades,
buttons, posters,</i>

911
00:45:52,949 --> 00:45:55,216
a show of maybe there's justice,

912
00:45:55,217 --> 00:45:56,350
because, I think, to me,

913
00:45:56,351 --> 00:45:58,120
it was just a huge injustice

914
00:45:58,121 --> 00:45:59,988
the fact they could even
do what they've done.

915
00:45:59,989 --> 00:46:02,924
The custody battle
was in full swing,

916
00:46:02,925 --> 00:46:05,928
and it was very dramatic
and scary for people.

917
00:46:05,929 --> 00:46:09,964
And as I interviewed Pete
and talked with him,

918
00:46:09,965 --> 00:46:12,755
<i>I realized at that time I'd
never met anybody like him</i>

919
00:46:13,001 --> 00:46:15,005
<i>in his
single-minded pursuit</i>

920
00:46:16,005 --> 00:46:17,872
of what he believed was right,

921
00:46:17,873 --> 00:46:20,875
and also, in the
flurry of emotions,

922
00:46:20,876 --> 00:46:24,879
I thought that meant that he
was the perfect guy for me,

923
00:46:24,880 --> 00:46:27,549
and so despite the fact that
I was writing about him

924
00:46:27,550 --> 00:46:29,384
and he should be my subject,

925
00:46:29,385 --> 00:46:31,587
I broke the first rule
of journalism

926
00:46:31,588 --> 00:46:33,955
and fell in love
with my subject.

927
00:46:33,956 --> 00:46:35,991
So we started dating,

928
00:46:35,992 --> 00:46:39,995
<i>and in our
emotional ridiculousness,</i>

929
00:46:39,996 --> 00:46:41,495
<i>got married
really quite quickly,</i>

930
00:46:41,496 --> 00:46:44,098
<i>within months of my moving here.</i>

931
00:46:44,099 --> 00:46:46,301
But it was okay.

932
00:46:46,302 --> 00:46:48,270
It was okay for what
was going on there.

933
00:46:48,271 --> 00:46:51,205
And so we
traversed this together,

934
00:46:51,206 --> 00:46:53,442
and I had...
created for myself

935
00:46:53,443 --> 00:46:55,444
the additional burden of
trying to be a journalist

936
00:46:55,445 --> 00:46:58,159
and separate my personal
feelings from my job.

937
00:47:10,759 --> 00:47:13,199
<i>Two federal courts have
sided with the government,</i>

938
00:47:13,200 --> 00:47:14,830
<i>saying Sue should
stay in the box</i>

939
00:47:15,030 --> 00:47:17,531
<i>because there's no proof the
dinosaur is being damaged there.</i>

940
00:47:17,532 --> 00:47:19,267
In another federal court,

941
00:47:19,268 --> 00:47:22,604
they're still arguing over
who actually owns the bones.

942
00:47:22,605 --> 00:47:25,374
The intensity reaction
while the court case

943
00:47:25,375 --> 00:47:27,209
was going on
really surprised me.

944
